From d1ddcb60f70797e734481cda180595c20c1d2ca0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Witold=20Bo=C5=82t?= <witold.bolt@jit.team>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 11:13:56 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 11/17] v3dv: guard degenerate zero-tile CL job at submit
 (vkQuake first-frame NULL deref)

A V3DV CL job whose frame tiling has a zero dimension (width, height or
layers) computes a zero-size tile-state BO; v3dv_bo_alloc(0) returns NULL,
and handle_cl_job() then dereferences job->tile_state->offset and Data-Aborts
(far=0x24 == offsetof(struct v3dv_bo, offset)). vkQuake's no-WSI 2D frame path
hit exactly this at the first vkQueueSubmit (tile_alloc valid at the 0x2000
zero-tile floor, tile_state NULL).

Guard queue_handle_job (under __phoenix__) to skip a GPU_CL job with a NULL
tile_state and return VK_SUCCESS: a zero-tile job has nothing for the binner
or renderer to do, and skipping it lets the real render job in the same submit
proceed. Add a one-shot v3dv_job_start_frame diagnostic naming the zero-dim
source (and whether it is the device noop job, cmd_buffer==NULL) so the
offending op (render area vs meta copy/clear/blit) is identifiable from a boot log.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_cmd_buffer.c | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_queue.c      | 24 ++++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 40 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_cmd_buffer.c b/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_cmd_buffer.c
index 4db0298232d..cd1dabe1531 100644
--- a/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_cmd_buffer.c
+++ b/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_cmd_buffer.c
@@ -521,6 +521,22 @@ v3dv_job_start_frame(struct v3dv_job *job,
 {
    assert(job);
 
+#if defined(__phoenix__)
+   /* Diagnostic: a frame started with a zero dimension yields zero tiles, a
+    * zero-size tile-state BO (NULL), and a NULL deref at submit time. Name the
+    * source once so the offending op (render area vs meta copy/clear/blit) is
+    * identifiable from a boot log. cmd_buffer == NULL marks the device noop job. */
+   if (width == 0 || height == 0 || layers == 0) {
+      static bool warned_zero = false;
+      if (!warned_zero) {
+         mesa_logw("v3dv: v3dv_job_start_frame with zero dimension "
+                   "(w=%u h=%u layers=%u, cmd_buffer=%p) -> no tile state\n",
+                   width, height, layers, (void *)job->cmd_buffer);
+         warned_zero = true;
+      }
+   }
+#endif
+
    /* Start by computing frame tiling spec for this job assuming that
     * double-buffer mode is disabled.
     */
diff --git a/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_queue.c b/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_queue.c
index d1b2e4d0c97..fbce1015a3d 100644
--- a/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_queue.c
+++ b/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_queue.c
@@ -998,6 +998,30 @@ queue_handle_job(struct v3dv_queue *queue,
       job->needs_bcl_sync = job->type == V3DV_JOB_TYPE_GPU_CL;
    }
 
+#if defined(__phoenix__)
+   /* Skip a degenerate CL job that has no tile state. A CL job's tile state is
+    * allocated from the frame tiling (layers * tiles_x * tiles_y); when one of
+    * those dimensions is zero the tile-state size is zero and v3dv_bo_alloc()
+    * returns NULL (see v3dv_job_allocate_tile_state / v3d_tile_alloc_sizes).
+    * handle_cl_job() then dereferences job->tile_state->offset and faults. Such a
+    * job (a zero-extent meta copy/clear/blit, or an empty render area) has nothing
+    * for the binner or renderer to do, so dropping it is correct and lets the real
+    * render job in the same submit proceed. Without this guard the no-WSI vkQuake
+    * 2D frame path hit a NULL-tile_state CL job at the first vkQueueSubmit and
+    * Data-Aborted in handle_cl_job (far=0x24 == offsetof v3dv_bo, offset). */
+   if (job->type == V3DV_JOB_TYPE_GPU_CL && job->tile_state == NULL) {
+      static bool warned = false;
+      if (!warned) {
+         mesa_logw("v3dv: skipping degenerate CL job with no tile state "
+                   "(zero-extent frame: w=%u h=%u layers=%u draws=%u)\n",
+                   job->frame_tiling.width, job->frame_tiling.height,
+                   job->frame_tiling.layers, job->draw_count);
+         warned = true;
+      }
+      return VK_SUCCESS;
+   }
+#endif
+
    switch (job->type) {
    case V3DV_JOB_TYPE_GPU_CL:
       return handle_cl_job(queue, job, counter_pass_idx, sync_info);
-- 
